

	 
      " 'Rabbi,' complained a bachelor, 'I thought it is written that everyone has a basherte, a partner destined by heaven. why have i never found mine?'  "The Rabbi looked at him with his penetrating eyes and then replied, 'you did find her, but when you saw her you thought her nose too long and passed her up.' "  - from  The Commited Life  by Rebbetzin Esther Jungreis
     

    
